  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Multinational - Transboundary Water Resources Infrastructures Development Study</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The African Union Commission (AUC) received at &#x20AC; 1.2 million grant to finance the establishment of a strategic intervention framework for the development of regional and continental transboundary hydraulic infrastructure, based on a common development vision and sector policies; and for the establishment of an investment programme for transboundary hydraulic infrastructure around priorities defined by the basin organisations and regional economic organisations. This project seeks to foster socioeconomic development by improving access to water infrastructure and services in Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The beneficiaries of the study include the Basin Organisations and the Regional Economic Communities (REC) of the five sub-regions of the continent: North Africa (UMA,CEN-SAD); West Africa (ECOWAS, CEN-SAD); Central Africa (ECCAS), East Africa (COMES, EAC, IGAD), Southern Africa (COMESA, SADC). These Basin Organisations and RECs, working closely with their states and populations, will be responsible for the effective implementation of the results of the PIDA study in their respective sub-regions and basins.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objectives of the TWR infrastructure development study are to enable African decisionmakers to: i) establish a strategic framework for the development of regional and continental water establish a TWR infrastructure investment programme around priorities established by Basin infrastructure, based on a shared development vision, strategic objectives and sector policies; ii) Organisations and Regional Economic Communities (RECs); and iii) prepare an implementation.</narrative>
  </description>
